## Components

- Named exports (`export function ComponentName`); PascalCase files (`ComponentName.tsx`).
- Define `Props` (or `interface Props`) above the component; use destructured props.
- Order: hooks → callbacks → derived (useMemo) → effects → return.
- Use `StyleSheet.create` at bottom of file.
- Never use inline functions in the return block; instead use named functions wrapped in `useCallback`.

```tsx
type Props = { variant?: keyof typeof styles };
export function StyledText({ variant = "regular", ...rest }: Props) {
  const isRtl = useIsRtl();
  const textStyles = useMemo(() => [...], []);
  return <Animated.Text style={textStyles} {...rest} />;
}
const styles = StyleSheet.create({ ... });
```

## Hooks

- camelCase with `use` prefix (`useExample.ts`) for hook name.
- File name matches hook name.
- Define `Props` (or `interface Props`) above the component; use destructured props.
- Order: hooks → callbacks → derived (useMemo) → effects → return.
- All returned values should be memoized.
- A testing file should be nested as a sibling next to the hook file, testing all functionality of the hook. (`useExample.test.ts`)
